indonesian food and the scene at this location is excellent. normally i would have posted a pic but food looked so good i couldn't stop. the service was very friendly and kind.
My top spot for quality indonesian food. do yourself a favor and try this place. the service was very helpful and welcoming. the bill was appropriate for the quality.
Delicious meal, first time ordering but will definitely order again. Everything came super hot and fresh and very quickly. Great place.

I was so happy to discover Java. Could it be the only Indonesian Rijsttafel restaurant in Brooklyn? No matter, it’s a delightful experience for two or a larger group. Plenty of options beyond the Rijsttafel to make it a worthy choice for solo dinner too.
A fav location for Indonesian food. Got there about three, it wasn't crowded. Certainly worth a return trip. Prices were average for the menu. Menu is like a cafe in Boston I liked.
A top scene for quality indonesian food. Certainly worth a return trip. Prices were decent.
DELICIOUS, Delicious, Delicious! Great Indonesia food
A top place for Indonesian food. The food was tasty. Looking forward to coming back with my coworkers. The bill was average for the menu.

Excellent food.

It was super delicious! We were craving Indonesian food and nothing disappointed. We had the bakwan (corn fritter), terong belado (a crispy eggplant) and the rendang, and we got way too excited and stuffed ourselves. Will definitely be coming back.

This place has a very friendly and homely feel. It is seemingly the only decent indonesian cuisine kitchen in the area. If you've never experienced Indonesian food and would like to give it a try this is the place to do it. Take my advice and order the tapas (chef tasting menu) which is a combination of 15 plates being served on a warming plate, quite inexpensive, and will easily fill two people. The fried banana dessert is AMAZING!

The food is delicious and the service outstanding. Highly recommended!  I recently ordered by phone, unsure if my South Brooklyn apartment was even within their delivery zone. In fact, it wasn't, but the owner said that they would still deliver to me. When the food arrived, a small item was missing but I did not mind. Frankly I was grateful they delivered to me in the first place, especially during lockdown.  The next day, the owner called me to tell me she had remembered that morning about the missing item and insisted on redelivering it! In addition, she included a whole extra (very yummy) dish as an apology!  Looking forward to having the Rijsttafel and much more on the menu when they reopen!

Food was very good and service was also very personal since the owner is the one serving the food along with one waiter. They are definitely understaffed because the food took very long time to prepare.

We came here after a day of only two bags of Cheetos, bread and an egg fully expecting good, Indonesian cooking. We were greeted with a cold interior, barely warmer than outside. The food took a long time to come, they were low on staff so it’s understandable, (we arrived around 7). The soup we ordered came barely hot, though it was delicious, we could’ve definitely enjoyed it more if we weren’t slightly shivering or if the soup was hot. Then came our food, my mother ordered the “rendang” beef, it had a pleasant aftertaste though the beef was way too overcooked and had become stiff. My sister ordered the, I’m really bad with names but here is my recollection of it, crispy fried chicken with a hot and sour sauce. This was surprisingly good. I, unfortunately, ordered the “kalio ayam”  which took a little bit more time to cook, when it arrived , the chicken was rubbery and I had to really force it in. After paying more attention to it, I saw that part of it was raw.  This wasn’t the best of situations. So my final verdict, the food’s concept is really good, they have an idea of what to make but they don’t know how to make it. I suggest you call before and ask how long you would have to wait for your food to make sure you don’t end up in our situation.
The $52 tasting menu for 2 is an unbeatable deal. Cute spot--when I went the cook was also working as the only waiter.
We had an amazing time eating here! The food/drinks were mind blowing and the service was perfect. Highly recommend it!
The food is excellent and the staff are very nice! Super fast service and the environment is cozy. Lots of vegetarian options! What a hidden gem I’m so happy we found them. Will definitely be back!
Friendly service. We ordered the tasting menu (15 dishes) for 2. The food was great and there was more than enough (took a to-go box).
Really great service and price and portions. Great options for veg and meat people.
You can add extra spice if you ask for it. Great sauce. Unfortunately they ran out of lamb meat, but my friend got the last portion haha

Indonesian food and the atmosphere at this location is super good. Very appetizing. Next time I'll be back with my relatives. Bring your hunger - portions are generous. Food is similar to a cafe in Portland I liked.
Loved the food, pretty aunthetic. Get the fish curry and the sliced leg of lamb. The lady working is adorable too. Definitely will come back!
The sate is unbelievable.  The chicken was tender and I was licking the sauce off the plate. The Tumis was also delicious and fully vegetarian. It's quiet and small, but you'll love it guaranteed.

Bombbbbb fooddddd. For real. This place is sooo good. I went there on a cold rainy night, and found myself feasting on a super comforting steamy bowl of curry goodness. Needless to say, it really hit the spot. The spot is intimate, and cozy. I will be going back!
The waitress was amazing, almost grandmother like, the food tasted real and the aphnosphere was nice

Flavorful, mildly spicy, delicious food in pleasant atmosphere. We had the 17 tapas pre-fix, with veggie, fish, chicken, and beef selections, starting with traditional chicken soup for the first course. We are picky new yorkers, that are hard to please. It was our first visit here, and we will def be back! Tip: we got there little past 5 on a Saturday while most tables were available. When we were leaving at 7, there was already a line. Get there earlier if you dont want to wait or call in advance, they seem to be taking reservations.

Really amazing food. Super delicious and home made. Only reason for a 4 not a 5. And maybe I should give a 5, service was extremely slow. But how can you be upset with a hard working restaurant owner, very cute older lady being the only waiter and server and taking phone orders and bussing from the kitchen to the table and cleaning up, setting tables , bringing menu and bringing the check. I mean, 10 tables. All done by the old lady, while her daughter in law was cooking the meals  Got to love it. But might need to reap the benefits of an amazing restaurant and hire someone for weekend nights. It could deter people that don't have 3 hours to sit and finish a meal.
Kare Ayam chicken is great. Had it many times
I had no clue this gem of a restaurant existed in my neighborhood.

First time trying Indonesian food so I’m by no means an expert on authenticity. However, we did the prefix 15 course sampler which allowed us to try a a little of everything and was very pleasantly surprised. Would’ve rated this place a 5 star but didn’t love the peanut sauce and the entrees came out not as hot or warm as I would’ve liked. Will come back again.

I highly recommend this place. The staff is beyond friendly and accomodating, a family restaurant I would guess. The food is delicious, I'd really suggest trying the lumpia, the sweet and spicy sauces combine w it really well.  And the Garada drink just became my new favorite weakness. It's like drinking in a summer vacation on the beach. The atmosphere is something I would really recommend for date night - the dark panelling and chandelier make it feel really romantic and intimate. It's not huge but it's cozy, sweet. Probably good to catch up with you friends too - I think I saw tapas version of the menu, though I haven't tried it. But seriously friendly comfortable restaurant w well made food.  Confirmed!!! Family restaurant here for 26 years and the owner ( one of the cooks too) is the SWEETEST lady.  Seriously, check this place out, it's adorable!!!
Great curry chicken Here. my favorite .!!
Wonderful! Service warm and attentive, food amazing, atmosphere cool.
